##The World Health Organization has raised the global risk level for the outbreak, Bill Gates, saying that new pneumonia could become a once in a century pandemic

The World Health Organization (WHO) has raised the global risk level of a new pneumonia outbreak from "high risk" to "very high" , WHO director-general Tan Desai announced at a regular media meeting on February 28(Geneva time) . Tan said that this is because the new pneumonia outbreak is now spreading in many countries around the world, with more than 4,300 confirmed cases outside China and an increasing number of countries still experiencing the disease, thus raising the global risk level.

In an earlier media conference, Tan Desai has said that the global epidemic prevention and control into a "decisive moment. ". WHO calls on every country to be prepared for all eventualities, and no country should take the chance that its own cases will not occur.

Whether the COVID-19 has reached the level of a "pandemic" is also a matter of public concern. In fact, World Health Organization's decision to use the word pandemic to describe an epidemic does not represent a change in the alert level, but depends on the geographic spread of the virus and the severity of the disease it causes, and Its impact on society as a whole.

We should be prepared for the possibility of a global epidemic, Tandser said. But the key question is not what word to use to describe an outbreak. Using "pandemic" or not does not interfere with any single infection or help save anyone's life. It is time for all nations, communities, families and individuals to focus on getting ready.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Figure | who retweets UN Social Media Feed: "Now is not the time to panic. Now is the time to be ready. " (Source: Twitter)

But in the Bill Gates's view, the new coronavirus could be a once-in-a-century "pandemic" . Also on February 28, he published an opinion piece in the Journal The New England Journal of Medicine: "coping with a once-in-a-century epidemic of Covid-19 -- Foshan? " In the face of a pandemic, the Bill Gates argued that, world leaders have an important responsibility to both accelerate innovation and research and save more lives, and to work together to improve the global pandemic response in the long run.

In any crisis, he says, leaders always have two equally important responsibilities: to solve the problem at hand and to prevent it from happening again. The new coronary pneumonia epidemic is a case in point. We need not only to save lives, but also to improve the overall response to outbreaks. The former is more urgent, while the latter is vital in the long run.

Bill and the Melinda Gates, which have focused in recent years on improving the world's ability to respond to outbreaks, have devoted significant resources to preparing the world for such outbreaks, the article said. In the current crisis, the Bill Gates hopes it won't get much worse, but people should be prepared.

There are two main reasons for the threat of NCP: On the one hand, NCP can cause death in healthy adults in addition to those who already have health problems. Current data suggest a case-fatality rate of about 1% for the new type of pneumonia, which is between the 1957 pandemic (0.6% case-fatality rate) and the 1918 pandemic (2% case-fatality rate) , suggesting that it is several times more severe than the typical seasonal flu.

On the other hand, the new coronavirus is highly contagious. The average infected person will infect 2-3 people, resulting in an exponential increase. And there is strong evidence that it can be transmitted in people with mild to no symptoms. That means it will be harder to control than Middle East Respiratory Syndrome (MERS) and SARS, which are transmitted only by symptomatic patients and with much less transmission, and Atypical pneumonia.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Bill Gates said on social media that the new coronavirus may be a once in a century "pandemic" , but the good news is that there are steps we can take now to mitigate its impact, and help us respond more effectively to the next pandemic; a link to this article was later posted (Source: Twitter) 

The Bill Gates stressed that national and local governments, as well as public health agencies, should take action in the coming weeks to control the spread of the new outbreak. And, in addition to protecting their citizens, governments in a position to do so should help low-and middle-income countries prepare for an epidemic.

"Many low-and middle-income countries already have very weak health systems, and COVID-19 can quickly overwhelm them. Moreover, since richer countries will naturally put the interests of their own citizens first, poorer countries will have less political and economic capital to gain support,"he said, "By preparing countries in Africa and South Asia, we can not only save lives, but also slow the global spread of the virus. "

At the same time, he also called for speeding up the treatment of new pneumonia and vaccine development work.

The Bill Gates, through Bill and the Melinda Gates, has poured billions of dollars into supporting the global response to the new pneumonia outbreak, with up to $100 million to be spent, a large part of this will go to supporting low-and middle-income countries. Supported by the Wellcome Trust and the Bill & Melinda Gates Foundation, the Pandemic Preparedness Innovation Alliance (CEPI) , an organization that aims to prevent and control epidemics by accelerating vaccine development, eight promising vaccine candidates are now in preparation for clinical trials. If one or more of these vaccines prove safe and effective in animal models, they could be ready for large-scale clinical trials as early as June.

After the Bill Gates wrote its views and recommendations on the epidemic, it also offered a view on systemic issues at the macro level, saying that adjustments still needed to be made to ensure a more efficient response to the next pandemic. For example, helping low, and middle income countries strengthen their health care systems; creating a worldwide database of cases and requiring countries to share information; and building a system that can rapidly develop safe and effective vaccines and antiviral drug, to ensure rapid approval, and to achieve mass production.

In addition to these technical solutions, he said that change would require diplomatic efforts, and that the development of antiviral drug and vaccines would involve a large number of clinical trials and licensing agreements across national borders, and that international cooperation and data sharing should be promoted. "We should use the global platform to push for a rapid consensus on research priorities and test options for promising vaccine candidates and antiviral drug, " the Bill Gates said.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Figure | Bill and the Melinda Gates's $53.8 billion endowment over the past 20 years (Source: Bill and Melinda Gates Foundation)

To be sure, all advice has to do with money. He says governments need to invest because pandemic-related products are very high-risk investments, and public money helps to minimise the risk to drug companies, thus ensuring they are able to work full time. And given the economic costs of the epidemic, even if the investment in fighting the pandemic is not small, it is necessary to solve the problem.

Finally, he stressed: the Government and industry need to come to an agreement, "during a pandemic, vaccines and antiviral drug should not simply be sold to the highest bidder, but should be made available at affordable prices to those at the heart of the epidemic and those most in need, " he said, it is also the right strategy to stop transmission and prevent the spread of the epidemic.

As the epidemic spread, president Donald Trump, however, told the 28th Conservative Political Action Conference (CPAC) , an annual meeting of Political Conservative activists and elected officials across the country, that current concerns about the spread of COVID-19 were "a new hoax. " At the same time, the crowd reported a lower than the United States statistics confirmed the number of infected patients.

The speech drew criticism from many Americans on social media, and online criticism of Donald Trump's lack of attention to public health issues. Donald Trump's 2021 budget proposal to Congress in mid-february began with a 7% ($2.942 billion) cut to $36.965 billion from the National Institutes of Health.

Biomedical Research Groups in the United States at the time said they were very upset about the budget proposal. "This is going to be a devastating blow to biomedical research in the United States, " McKinney, Chief Science Officer of the Association of American Medical Schools, said on social media

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Donald Trump's claim that COVID-19 are a "hoax" has been derided by Americans on social media (Twitter) 

The Washington Post has just reported that Oregon has its first case of an unidentified new coronavirus infection, following two cases in California. State health officials said, the patient is from Washington County, has not been to the site of the outbreak, and has not been in contact with a known new pneumonia patient.

It is hoped that governments will heed World Health Organization's call and heed the advice of the Bill Gates to contain what is likely to be a "pandemic" of pneumonia, which continues to spread around the world. As the Bill Gates reminds at the end of the article, "global leaders should act now, without delay. "
